Lets try to do the summary by site, day for the 2017 data for RH and Temperature

head(pws %>%mutate(HR= format(tsfmt,"%H"),DATE=format(tsfmt,"%Y-%m-%d")) %>% group_by(Plot,DATE,HR) %>% summarise(minHrlyTemp = min(Temp),maxHrlyTemp = max(Temp),meanHrlyTemp = mean(Temp),minHrlyRH = min(RH),maxHrlyRH = max(RH),meanHrlyRH = mean(RH)) %>% as.data.frame())

Lets write to CSV

pws %>%mutate(HR= format(tsfmt,"%H"),DATE=format(tsfmt,"%Y-%m-%d")) %>% group_by(Plot,DATE,HR) %>% summarise(minHrlyTemp = min(Temp),maxHrlyTemp = max(Temp),meanHrlyTemp = mean(Temp),minHrlyRH = min(RH),maxHrlyRH = max(RH),meanHrlyRH = mean(RH)) %>% as.data.frame() %>% write.csv("data/Hobo-2017-Summary-Hourly.csv")

Now, lets create the daily file. We can follow the same, but now summarize by DATE

pws %>%mutate(HR= format(tsfmt,"%H"),DATE=format(tsfmt,"%Y-%m-%d")) %>% group_by(Plot,DATE) %>% summarise(minHrlyTemp = min(Temp),maxHrlyTemp = max(Temp),maxHrlyTemp = max(Temp),minHrlyRH = min(RH),maxHrlyRH = max(RH),meanHrlyRH = mean(RH)) %>% as.data.frame() %>% write.csv("data/Hobo-2017-Summary-Daily.csv")

Plot the number of collections by day

ht2017 %>% mutate(site = as.factor(Plot)) %>%
group_by(site) %>%
summarise(total = n()) %>% ggplot(aes(x=site,fill=total)) + 
geom_bar() + 
theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1))

Different way of looking at same, we expect for each plot 24 points for a day, so that makes it 24*365 (approx 8760 points for a site) . We get 2 by site every hour.

ht2017 %>%  mutate(site = as.factor(Plot)) %>%
group_by(site) %>%
summarise(total = n()) %>% ggplot(aes(x=site,y=total)) + 
geom_point() + 
theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1))

Issue with 1349 collection, so have less than half of the half required points, so we can drop it from analysis.

Now, lets look at the unusually high temperatures

ht2017 %>% group_by(dt)  %>% summarise(avg_temp=mean(meanHrlyTemp)) %>% ggplot(aes(dt,avg_temp)) +
geom_point() + geom_smooth(alpha=.2, size=2)

Lets look at mean temperatures by month

ht2017$site<- as.factor(ht2017$Plot)
ht2017 %>% filter(!(Plot %in% c(1342))) %>% mutate(MONTH= format(dt,"%m"),DAY= format(dt,"%d")) %>% filter(MONTH %in% c('01','02','03','04','05','06','07','08','09','10','11','12')) %>% group_by(site,MONTH,DAY) %>%
    summarise(
              min_temp = min(meanHrlyTemp),
              max_temp = max(meanHrlyTemp),
              mean_temp = max(meanHrlyTemp),
              diu_fluct = max_temp - min_temp ,
              total = n()) %>% ggplot(aes(site,mean_temp, color=MONTH)) + geom_point() +  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1)) + ggtitle("Mean temperatures by Month - Site n Month - 2017") + xlab("Site") + ylab("Measure of Magnitude")

Looks ok, lets look at daily Diurnal fluctuation

ht2017$site<- as.factor(ht2017$Plot)
ht2017 %>% filter(!(Plot %in% c(1342))) %>% mutate(MONTH= format(dt,"%m"),DAY= format(dt,"%d")) %>% filter(MONTH %in% c('01','02','03','04','05','06','07','08','09','10','11','12')) %>% group_by(site,MONTH,DAY) %>%
    summarise(
              min_temp = min(meanHrlyTemp),
              max_temp = max(meanHrlyTemp),
              diu_fluct = max_temp - min_temp ,
